## 5. Tables for Quick Reference

### Rendering Frame Steps
| Step | Component Involved | Action | Dependencies | Performance Notes |
|------|--------------------|--------|--------------|-------------------|
| 1 | Engine, HardwareDetector | Detect vendor and init paths | VkPhysicalDeviceProperties | Ensures compatibility |
| 2 | SceneManager, ResourceManager | Load data, allocate buffers | MultiViewImages, VkBuffer | Prepares Gaussians |
| 3 | Renderer, FlashGSSplatter | Optimize and rasterize Gaussians | cudaStream_t | 4x speedup |
| 4 | Renderer, OptiXRayTracer | Build AS, trace rays | OptixPipeline | Handles reflections |
| 5 | Renderer, DenoiseModule | Apply AI denoiser | OptixDenoiser | Reduces samples |
| 6 | Renderer, Upscaler | Super resolution | Streamline/FidelityFX | 2-8x FPS boost |
| 7 | Renderer | Present via swapchain | VkSwapchainKHR | Final output |

### Upscaling Paths Comparison
| Upscaler | Integration | API | Vendor Support | Benefits | Limitations |
|----------|-------------|-----|----------------|----------|-------------|
| DLSS | Streamline plugins | Framework | NVIDIA RTX | Up to 8x FPS | NVIDIA-only |
| FSR | FidelityFX dispatch | C++ HLSL | Broad | 2x FPS | Lower quality on non-AMD |

## 6. Best Practices and Enforcement
- Use Vulkan-Hpp for safe API calls.
- Implement with CMake, CUDA Toolkit, OptiX SDK.
- Prioritize energy efficiency with GPU-driven rendering.
- Enforce via code reviews and Cursor AI.